      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CUMULATE (1) looks close to another win after hitting the frame in a 1.3 lengths second (22.44) in a Grade 5 at Geelong. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Can find winning form. RUMOUR I'M BROKE (3) sailed across from an outside draw last start to score an all-the-way win (16.84) at this track in a T3 Grade 6 over 300m. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. Should feature again. CALLAHAN (5) is a sprinter who excels over the short dashes. Finished fourth latest over 390m at Shepparton (22.52) in a Grade 5. Goes very well at the journey winning one races. Strong form has emerged from his last run. Should be about the money. HE'S A COLLINDA (8) placed last time (20.04) at Traralgon in a Grade 4/5, finishing second and beaten 3 lengths. Has already won two times from this draw.",
